The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 24: Food inflation rose to 16.9 per cent in mid-June because of high prices of pulses, fruits, vegetables and milk, putting pressure on the RBI to hike key policy rates.The price of pulses for the week ended June 12 was higher by 34.14 per cent over the corresponding week last year, while milk became dearer by 21.12 per cent.                             
	 New Delhi, June 24: Domestic and international air fares will attract service tax of Rs 100 and Rs 500, respectively, from next month. The government said it would charge service tax on air travel, starting July 1. Most airlines, however, said they would not raise fares as of now.                            
	 Bangalore, June 24: The follow-on public offer of Hindustan Copper is expected to hit the market in September-October, chairman Shakeel Ahmed said today.                             
	 New Delhi, June 24: The government today awarded seven coal-bed-methane (CBM) blocks for exploration, with Essar Oil bagging four of them. The Cabinet Committee on Economic Affairs has also awarded one oil exploration block under the New Exploration Licensing Policy.                            
	 New Delhi, June 24: Diagnostic chain Metropolis Healthcare today said private equity firm Warburg Pincus had bought out the entire stake of ICICI Ventures in it for $85-million. ICICI Ventures has completely divested its holding in the company, which it acquired in 2006.
                                                                                                                          
